cpqIoDrvInfoSubVendorPartNumber.description: Sub-vendor system part number of this device.

cpqIoDrvInfoSparesPartNumber.name: cpqIoDrvInfoSparesPartNumber
cpqIoDrvInfoSparesPartNumber.description: The spares part number of this IO Drive.

cpqIoDrvInfoAssemblyNumber.name: cpqIoDrvInfoAssemblyNumber
cpqIoDrvInfoAssemblyNumber.description: The assembly number of this IO Drive (HW revision).

cpqIoDrvInfoDriverVersion.description: Device driver version of this IO Drive.

cpqIoDrvInfoUID.description: IO Drive UID written at format time.

cpqIoDrvInfoState.name: cpqIoDrvInfoState
cpqIoDrvInfoState.description: The current state of the attached client device. In order to function normally, the device must be in the 'attached' state. Quiescent states: attached = device is ready for normal use detached = device is stopped minimal = driver loaded but firmware needs updating error = device is not working properly Transitional states: attaching = device is initializing scanning = part of device initialization detaching = device is stopping formatting = the format operation is in process updating = the firmware is being updated Operations: attach = make device operational detach = take device off-line format = re-formats device update = firmware update Device state must be minimal or detached to update the firmware and must be detached in order format.

cpqIoDrvInfoClientDeviceName.name: cpqIoDrvInfoClientDeviceName
cpqIoDrvInfoClientDeviceName.description: The name of the attached client device.

cpqIoDrvInfoBeacon.name: cpqIoDrvInfoBeacon
cpqIoDrvInfoBeacon.description: Writing a true value here will turn on the LED flashing beacon for visual card identification. A false value will turn the LED beacon off.

cpqIoDrvInfoPCIAddress.name: cpqIoDrvInfoPCIAddress
cpqIoDrvInfoPCIAddress.description: IO Drive address on the PCI bus.

cpqIoDrvInfoPCISubdeviceID.description: The PCI subdevice ID of this IO Drive.

cpqIoDrvInfoPCIVendorID.name: cpqIoDrvInfoPCIVendorID
cpqIoDrvInfoPCIVendorID.description: The subvendor ID of this IO Drive.

cpqIoDrvInfoPCISubvendorID.name: cpqIoDrvInfoPCISubvendorID
cpqIoDrvInfoPCISubvendorID.description: The subvendor ID of this IO Drive.

cpqIoDrvInfoPCISlot.name: cpqIoDrvInfoPCISlot
cpqIoDrvInfoPCISlot.description: The PCI slot number of this IO Drive.

cpqIoDrvInfoWearoutIndicator.description: A true condition indicates that the device has surpassed the wearout threshold.

cpqIoDrvInfoFlashbackIndicator.name: cpqIoDrvInfoFlashbackIndicator
cpqIoDrvInfoFlashbackIndicator.description: A true condition indicates that flashback redundancy is degraded.

cpqIoDrvInfoNonWritableIndicator.name: cpqIoDrvInfoNonWritableIndicator
cpqIoDrvInfoNonWritableIndicator.description: A true condition indicates that the device is no longer writable because it has surpassed the read-only threshold..

cpqIoDrvInfoCurrentTemp.name: cpqIoDrvInfoCurrentTemp
cpqIoDrvInfoCurrentTemp.description: The current temperature of the device in Celsius.

cpqIoDrvInfoPercentLifeRemaining.name: cpqIoDrvInfoPercentLifeRemaining
cpqIoDrvInfoPercentLifeRemaining.description: An estimate of the health of the drive expressed as the remaining percentage of drive life.

cpqIoDrvInfoShortTermWearoutDate.name: cpqIoDrvInfoShortTermWearoutDate
cpqIoDrvInfoShortTermWearoutDate.description: The date that the drive is estimated to reach the wearout threshold based on drive usage in the short-term interval.

cpqIoDrvInfoLongTermWearoutDate.name: cpqIoDrvInfoLongTermWearoutDate
cpqIoDrvInfoLongTermWearoutDate.description: The date that the drive is estimated to reach the wearout threshold based on drive usage in the long-term interval.

cpqIoDrvInfoShortTermNonWritableDate.name: cpqIoDrvInfoShortTermNonWritableDate
cpqIoDrvInfoShortTermNonWritableDate.description: The date that the drive is estimated to go non-writable based on drive usage in the short-term interval.

cpqIoDrvInfoLongTermNonWritableDate.name: cpqIoDrvInfoLongTermNonWritableDate
cpqIoDrvInfoLongTermNonWritableDate.description: The date that the drive is estimated to go non-writable based on drive usage in the long-term interval.

cpqIoDrvExtnTable.description: This table is extension of IO Drive information.

cpqIoDrvExtnEntry.description: Addiotnal Informaiton about IO Drive will be populated in this table.

cpqIoDrvExtnIndex.description: Unique number index for each IO Drive extension entries. There will be one-one mapping between cpqIoDrvExtnIndex and cpqIoDrvInfoIndex.

cpqIoDrvExtnTotalPhysicalCapacityU.name: cpqIoDrvExtnTotalPhysicalCapacityU
cpqIoDrvExtnTotalPhysicalCapacityU.description: The upper word of the total physical capacity in bytes.

cpqIoDrvExtnTotalPhysicalCapacityL.name: cpqIoDrvExtnTotalPhysicalCapacityL
cpqIoDrvExtnTotalPhysicalCapacityL.description: The lower word of the total physical capacity in bytes.

cpqIoDrvExtnUsablePhysicalCapacityU.name: cpqIoDrvExtnUsablePhysicalCapacityU
cpqIoDrvExtnUsablePhysicalCapacityU.description: The upper word of the usable physical capacity in bytes. This is space that is holding valid data, is erased and ready for writing or waiting to be reclaimed via garbage collection.

cpqIoDrvExtnUsablePhysicalCapacityL.name: cpqIoDrvExtnUsablePhysicalCapacityL
cpqIoDrvExtnUsablePhysicalCapacityL.description: The lower word of the usable physical capacity in bytes. This is space that is holding valid data, is erased and ready for writing or waiting to be reclaimed via garbage collection.

cpqIoDrvExtnUsedPhysicalCapacityU.name: cpqIoDrvExtnUsedPhysicalCapacityU
cpqIoDrvExtnUsedPhysicalCapacityU.description: The upper word used physical capacity in bytes. This is the space holding valid, current data.

cpqIoDrvExtnUsedPhysicalCapacityL.name: cpqIoDrvExtnUsedPhysicalCapacityL
cpqIoDrvExtnUsedPhysicalCapacityL.description: The lower word used physical capacity in bytes. This is the space holding valid, current data.

cpqIoDrvExtnTotalLogicalCapacityU.name: cpqIoDrvExtnTotalLogicalCapacityU
cpqIoDrvExtnTotalLogicalCapacityU.description: The upper word of the total logical capacity in bytes as formatted.

cpqIoDrvExtnTotalLogicalCapacityL.name: cpqIoDrvExtnTotalLogicalCapacityL
cpqIoDrvExtnTotalLogicalCapacityL.description: The lower word of the total logical capacity in bytes as formatted.

cpqIoDrvExtnAvailableLogicalCapacityU.name: cpqIoDrvExtnAvailableLogicalCapacityU
cpqIoDrvExtnAvailableLogicalCapacityU.description: The upper word of the available logical capacity in bytes.

cpqIoDrvExtnAvailableLogicalCapacityL.name: cpqIoDrvExtnAvailableLogicalCapacityL
cpqIoDrvExtnAvailableLogicalCapacityL.description: The lower word of the available logical capacity in bytes.

cpqIoDrvExtnBytesReadU.name: cpqIoDrvExtnBytesReadU
cpqIoDrvExtnBytesReadU.description: The upper word of the total number of bytes read since the device was formatted.

cpqIoDrvExtnBytesReadL.name: cpqIoDrvExtnBytesReadL
cpqIoDrvExtnBytesReadL.description: The lower word of the total number of bytes read since the device was formatted.

cpqIoDrvExtnPhysicalBytesWrittenU.name: cpqIoDrvExtnPhysicalBytesWrittenU
cpqIoDrvExtnPhysicalBytesWrittenU.description: The upper word of the total physical bytes written.

cpqIoDrvExtnPhysicalBytesWrittenL.name: cpqIoDrvExtnPhysicalBytesWrittenL
cpqIoDrvExtnPhysicalBytesWrittenL.description: The lower word of the total physical bytes written.

cpqIoDrvExtnLogicalBytesWrittenU.name: cpqIoDrvExtnLogicalBytesWrittenU
cpqIoDrvExtnLogicalBytesWrittenU.description: The upper word of the number of user data bytes written.

cpqIoDrvExtnLogicalBytesWrittenL.name: cpqIoDrvExtnLogicalBytesWrittenL
cpqIoDrvExtnLogicalBytesWrittenL.description: The lower word of the number of user data bytes written.

cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermStartDate.name: cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermStartDate
cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermStartDate.description: The start date used to characterize short-term drive usage.

cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermWindow.name: cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermWindow
cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermWindow.description: The number of hours in the short-term usage characterization window. If this value is non-zero, then the short-term start date will automatically track with the short-term end date by the number of hours specified.

cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermEndDate.name: cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermEndDate
cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermEndDate.description: The end date used to characterize short-term drive usage.

cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermEndDateFloat.name: cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermEndDateFloat
cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermEndDateFloat.description: Set this variable true to automatically have the short-term end date automatically updated to the present date.

cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermStartDate.name: cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermStartDate
cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermStartDate.description: The start date used to characterize long-term drive usage.

cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermWindow.name: cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermWindow
cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermWindow.description: The number of hours in the long-term usage characterization window. If this value is non-zero, then the long-term start date will automatically track with the long-term end date by the number of hours specified.

cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermEndDate.name: cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermEndDate
cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermEndDate.description: The end date used to characterize long-term drive usage.

cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermEndDateFloat.name: cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermEndDateFloat
cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermEndDateFloat.description: Set this variable true to automatically have the long-term end date automatically updated to the present date.

cpqIoDrvExtnWriteRateAutoCalc.name: cpqIoDrvExtnWriteRateAutoCalc
cpqIoDrvExtnWriteRateAutoCalc.description: Set this true to automatically calculate the long-term and short-term average write rate based on the start and end dates selected. Otherwise, the average write rate must be set manually.

cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermAvgU.name: cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermAvgU
cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermAvgU.description: The upper word of the short-term average write rate used to characterize drive usage. This will be automatically calculated based on short-term start and end dates if the auto calc value is true.

cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermAvgL.name: cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermAvgL
cpqIoDrvExtnShortTermAvgL.description: The lower word of the short-term average write rate used to characterize drive usage. This will be automatically calculated based on short-term start and end dates if the auto calc value is true.

cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermAvgU.name: cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermAvgU
cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermAvgU.description: The upper word of the long-term average write rate used to characterize drive usage. This will be automatically calculated based on long-term start and end dates if the auto calc value is true.

cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermAvgL.name: cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermAvgL
cpqIoDrvExtnLongTermAvgL.description: The lower word of the long-term average write rate used to characterize drive usage. This will be automatically calculated based on long-term start and end dates if the auto calc value is true.

cpqIoDrvExtnConfidenceInterval.name: cpqIoDrvExtnConfidenceInterval
cpqIoDrvExtnConfidenceInterval.description: This defines the confidence interval used to calculate the wearout and non-writable dates. Expressed as a percentage, this value reflects the confidence in the short and long-term averages used to characterize drive usage.

cpqIoDrvWearoutTrap.name: cpqIoDrvWearoutTrap
cpqIoDrvWearoutTrap.description: IO Drive begins to wear out. This trap signifies that the agent has detected a wear out of IO Drive configured with your system.

cpqIoDrvNonWritableTrap.name: cpqIoDrvNonWritableTrap
cpqIoDrvNonWritableTrap.description: IO Drive is not writeable due to excessive wear This trap signifies that IO Drive configured with system is not writeable due to excessive wear. User Action: Replace the existing IO Drive to make it writable.

cpqIoDrvFlashbackTrap.name: cpqIoDrvFlashbackTrap
cpqIoDrvFlashbackTrap.description: IO Drive flashback protection becomes degraded This trap signifies that IO Drive flashback protection configured with system is degraded.

cpqIoDrvTempHighTrap.name: cpqIoDrvTempHighTrap
cpqIoDrvTempHighTrap.description: Temperature sensor of IO Drive surpasses the threshold. This trap signifies that the temperature sensor of IO Drive configured with system surpasses the threshold configured.

cpqIoDrvTempOkTrap.name: cpqIoDrvTempOkTrap
cpqIoDrvTempOkTrap.description: Temperature sensor of IO Drive set below threshold. This trap signifies that the temperature sensor of IO Drive configured with system surpasses the threshold configured.

cpqIoDrvErrorTrap.name: cpqIoDrvErrorTrap
cpqIoDrvErrorTrap.description: IO Drive is in an error state.
